 be detailed. <p><html><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=237695"><img src="http://www.magicstuff.net/images/eronjsig.gif" width="360" height="100"></a></html></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/utuan00dorf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tuan00Dorf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 1329<br> <font color=#E9D756>(5/31/02 1:33:48 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9801.topic&index=1>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How do YOU solo?</span><hr size=1> I start off with Gloria's sig, then move on to Karin's.. Then, errr, wait a sec.. nm. <p>Tuan {Cupcakes} the Vicar</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/umalevant.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Malevant</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 180<br> <font color=#E9D756>(5/31/02 1:43:04 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9801.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How do YOU solo?</span><hr size=1> I solo by myself...<br><br>Actually, here goes...<br><br>I do a few different things, depending on the mood, the mob, and the zone.<br><br>1. DoT Rot.  Just snare, root, DoT and repeat.  This is easily done by myself when I have say, the mental capacity of a flower pot after a late night or long day.<br><br>2. Kiting.  I don't Quad, when a Ranger quads its called a train.  But I do single kite mobs around, and nuke them.  When you consider the caliber of Ranger nukes, this is not supremely effective, but it does get the job done on most mobs.<br><br>3. Fear Kiting.  I love this, although it only works with Animals as a Ranger.  This is probably by far the most efficient solo method, although chasing stuff around can get old rather quickly.<br><br>4. Tanking.  I usually use a Swarmcaller for slows when tanking, so that things get a bit easier in toe-to-toe.  Anything other than a low blue I generally do not do this exclusively on.<br><br>5. Arrow Kiting.  I never use this, I am too high for my arrows to do appreciable damage, and too low to have AM3/EQ for best effect.  However, I tend to intersperse whatever other methods I am using with a fair dosage of this, particularly when I am bored.<br><br>I almost never use exclusively one of the above on any single mob.  I typically try to use x amount of mana, and then tank it so that I take y amount of damage, working to keep the downtime for x and y roughly equal.  Having FM and 30% life really just means I get to med to full again, so I try to use enough mana to make it count.  Fear kiting is the exception.  Set any Ranger in a nest of animals and they will have a blast, and the mana costs primarily end up going to Heals for the brief durations when Fear has worn off.<br><br>I don't usually solo for experience grind, but when I do solo, those are the techniques I use.  I have lower Wis than I would like, so my mana pool is not as huge for me to play with, but I am working on getting gear to use to up it for various solo experiments.  Rangers, at least at the point I am at right now, can *almost* do a lot of solo styles, and by mixing and combining them I find things work out pretty well.  The variety keeps the repetition a bit more bearable, and I enjoy trying new things.  Not sure how representative I am of other Rangers, or higher end Rangers, but for me at 53 anyways, it works pretty good <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><center><IMG SRC=" http://www.unicorntrad.org/mal_sig.jpg"></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ujabener.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jabener</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 169<br> <font color=#E9D756>(5/31/02 2:15:21 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9801.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How do YOU solo?</span><hr size=1> I agree with Malevant, though i'm more of a tanking fan, and i've never felt a ranger's nukes (though powerful) are anywhere near efficient enough to kite with.  Back when animals actualy gave me xp i'd fear kite almost exclusively, to the envy of entire groups in OT ;D (ok ok so maybe i'm just imagining their envy, but almost always out-leveled them).  At level 51 I had the ability to move my cleric to a second account, which i did, and that pretty much set the tone for my soloing career, i'd tank a mob and have the cleric (un-grouped) heal me when i needed it, thus i had the mana to rebuff myself when i needed.  These days, at level 59 with earthcaller and swiftwind i generally only need my cleric to keep up a steady pace; i can generally solo on my own in OS and hold about 8-10 spawns.  of course, i ask for clarities from anyone i can... (please don't give me any other buffs unless you ask first, you may think you're helping, but a lot of the time it just ruins some plan of mine) my general method is tank a mob 'til it runs or i get below 2 bubbles of health - in which case i root it, back away, heal myself, and proceed to kill it.  Kiting, either bow or nuke/doting is pretty much out of the question, i think.  I only have about 70 wisdom, which means about 1300 mana, i think. my nuke does do 450 pts of damage, but the 250 mana it takes is way too much a cost, plus the spell only refreshes once every minute or so... my dots are only 300-350 pts, so that would just take *way* too long.  Arrows, although unlimited with a tolan's bracer.... I guess i could do it that way but it feels like a cheesy cop-out to me, as if i couldnt fight it like a *real* fighter.... i resort to it only when i'm extremely low on health and mana. <p>-Jabener Half-elven<BR>Ranger of Karana<BR><BR><center><img src="http://www.burningmoon.net/images/Jabener.jpg"></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/usubminadominatrix.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Submina Dominatrix</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 648<br> <font color=#E9D756>(5/31/02 2:23:48 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9801.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How do YOU solo?</span><hr size=1> I pull something that does not look too threatening<br><br>like a green or a light blue<br><br>I then proceed to auto attack it for about 5 to 10 minutes, possibly making myself a cup of tea in the meantime.<br><br>During this time I pray that I will live.<br><br>If I get low on health I leg it to a zone and count my lucky stars<br><br>if I win, I either use 40+ bandaids taking 15 seconds each to apply, or I go watch tv for 30 mins while my health regens...<br><br>That or I partner with a healing class, or my beastlord ;p <p>Baroness Submina Dominatrix<BR>60 Warrior<BR>Divine Grace<BR><p align="center"><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=6783><img border="0" src="http://www.zagato.demon.co.uk/eq/images/subsig.jpg" width="593" height="233"></A></p><BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ukidin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kidin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 123<br> <font color=#E9D756>(5/31/02 3:15:41 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9801.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How do YOU solo?</span><hr size=1> I pull dark blues with slow or root, depending if there is a possibility of grabbing 2 or not.<br><br>If it is a slow-pull:  I let the mob beat on me while I channel through w/ dot(s) first and JB bracer for the rest, with pet hasted and nipping at its heels.  Poking once or twice in between each cast.  If it is a caster, I'll skip the bracer, drop bearform, and slam while poking furiously w/ REIF to keep interrupting his casts.<br><br>If a root pull:  Back up to max range, dot poison, then nuke w/ Bracer until root breaks.  Re-root and repeat.  If using dog-dog, alternate taking the hits between him and myself to keep pet alive.  This is my general methodology when low on mana/health as I generally finish with more of each then when I started the pull.  If the area is obviously clear, I'll pull w/ a big nuke from max range instead, and root as he approaches whatever spot I want to keep him at.  If I know the mob has lots of HP (long battle), I'll dot disease also.<br><br>Both methods have very little down-time if done right.  I generally inter-mingle them for variety.<br><br>Take care,<br>Frekkels<br>Proud Member of Clan Battle Axe<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ukunorepo.showPublicProfile?language=EN>KunoRepo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 32<br> <font color=#E9D756>(5/31/02 4:18:10 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9801.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How do YOU solo?</span><hr size=1> Jabener couldn't tank her right arm!!  /hides<br><br>Monk class....get yer AC and HP's up high enough (fungi helps) and pull the mob.  Pray you can be faster then him =/<br><br>Eblan Shadowstyx<br>60 Iksar Monk<br>&quot;Why split these 3 mobs??  I have 2 chanters to kill!&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ubehomara.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Behomara</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 17<br> <font color=#E9D756>(5/31/02 4:21:46 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9801.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Soloing</span><hr size=1> Mostly kiting here. . .<br><br>Kiting singles:  pull with a snare, then nuke, run a lil, nuke again, etc etc until dead.  If snare resists, do a fast root until it sticks, back off and resnare until it sticks, then kite as normal.  If all fails, click jboots and hightail it outta there <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>Kiting multiples:  make sure jboots are on, find target, pull it with staff of temperate flux (insta-cast slight mr cr debuff), pull other targets while running from first, then either run em around til they're grouped, or just stop and let my rune shield absorb the damage to group em together.  If i live thru the massive attacks, run away again until they're far away enough for AE snare, cast snare, then kite using AE nukes, resnaring whenever paranoia sets in.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :b --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aengli