pan class=title> Re: Soloing</span><hr size=1> I use the pally certified method at level 53. Always Dark blue cons.<br><br>Find an undead camp.<br><br>Buff with Daring ( Helm ), Armor of Faith, Valor of Marr and Instrument of Nife. Med up.<br><br>Pull a single with Dismiss Undead. Undead tend to be non social in most camps.<br><br>Beat 10 shades out of it.<br><br>Heal to full with helm. Go again.<br><br>Exp - 1 blue an hour.<br><br><br>With KEI.<br><br>Buff with Valor, Instrument of Nife, Symbol of Pinzarn, Armor of Faith, Daring, Divine Favour and Divine Purpose.<br><br>Nuke undead mob with Dismiss.<br><br>Beat 10 shades out of it constantly casting Dismiss.<br><br>Kill mob with 4 bubbles of health remainining.<br><br>Use DW Gaunts to cast dispell on mob ( mana free pull )<br><br>Beat mob to death, no spells at all.<br><br>Heal to full ( usually 1/2 a bubble of mana )<br><br>Rinse and repeat. Every other mob gets blasted with no spells on the others.<br><br>Exp 2 blue per hour<br><br> <p><CENTER><A HREF="http://ak.lonelygamer.com"><IMG SRC="http://www.plattsflello.com/ryn.gif" BORDER=0></A></CENTER></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ufeldynn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Feldynn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 145<br> <font color=#E9D756>(5/31/02 5:57:35 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9801.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Soloing</span><hr size=1> Never really been much for soloing with my bard (59) but what I used to do is pull with snare, fear (maybe twist in self haste or a dot if I Can be bothered hehe) and melee the thing ineffectually till it dies or sometimes do snare/dot kiting but that's not all that fun / effective either LOL.<br><br>With my shama