ex=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Solo'ing</span><hr size=1> Hmm, toughie with the 2 main classes I play.<br>First the warrior, currently 53.<br>There is no real &quot;soloing&quot; with this class. I usually pick a light blue mob and beat the heck out of it. With right clickable buffs and no jboots it is simply unrealistic to even bother. Even with almost 3000hp unbuffed and 1000+AC I still find that I lose 2- 2 1/2 bubs of life and can only maybe kill 2 in a row without having to sit for 30-45 minutes for recovery.<br><br>My Cleric is almost the same situation but is a little more effective. She is currently 51.<br>I take her to DL, get a clarity and head for the undead fort near the FV tunnel. The skelly's do not aggro each other so I usually pull with a stun. I do this just in case they resist my root, I can recast.<br>So, they are stunned and rooted.. I then start laying my Banish Undead on them. Usually after the second cast root breaks, re-root. I can med anytime during the re-root but there is a lot of mobs roaming in that area so I watch my back and run it to zone if I get hit. I usually go down 2 bubs of mana on one mob if I do not med in between but I can kill 3-4 and then run to the FV tunnel to med up (safer spot).<br>This also works well in City of Mist if the golems have been cleared. You can sit at the first bridge and kill the undead through the gate and med by the zone. Even the Golems can be rooted and killed with Retribution. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ulurikeen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lurikeen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 752<br> <font color=#E9D756>(5/31/0